The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Riot relief

 New Delhi, Aug. 19: Families of those killed during the 1984 anti-Sikh riots will get a relief of about Rs 5 lakh, reports our special correspondent.

 A committee constituted by the Union home ministry and headed by the secretary (border management), D.K. Shankaran, to look into relief and rehabilitation of anti-Sikh riot victims decided this at its first meeting today.

 The meeting was unanimous that the families of the victims should be paid according to the 1996 decision of Delhi High Court. The compensation of Rs 3.5 lakh will now be around Rs 5 lakh including interest. 




